verbose_text: In addition, 3D slab encoding leads to increased SNR compared with conventional consecutive or interleaved multi-slice (MS) acquisitions.30 In contrast to conventional GRE- or SE based MRE sequences, which can be solely understood on the basis of phase contrast, the proposed technique depends on spin history effects and necessitates the analysis of echo pathways and their motion sensitivities.
evidence: 3D slab encoding leads to increased SNR
